TESTING ROUTES\
\
How to Test\
\
- MyTest class extends CamelTestSupport\
- setUp() method is for preparation										DEUTSCH WARNING, call super.setUp() once you have finished your own setup tasks\
- createRouteBuilder returns a RouteBuilder									return an instance of the route you wrote\
- in the test method (annotated with @Test)\
	get a mock end point that route will send data to using getMockEndpoint(mock uri)\
	use template which is a producer to send body, header, etc.\
	assert that the mock end point is satisfied in some way\
\
- if you want to debug routes then Override\
	isUseDebugger() method with return true\
	debugBefore() method if you want to see what is happening before processing step\
	debugAfter() method if you want to see what is happening after processing step\
\
 \
